name: Adding service with invalid openApi version fails

steps.name: Given SecurityServer login page is open
And Page is prepared to be tested
And User xrd logs in to SecurityServer with password secret
When Rest service dialog is opened and OpenApi spec is set to "http://mock-server:1080/test-services/testopenapi_invalid_version.yaml" and service code "testOas31x"
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-url-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-url-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='service-code-text-field']/By.xpath: .//input") should be(empty: attribute value="" and exact text "")
Then Dialog data is saved and error message "Unsupported OpenAPI version. Only versions 3.0.x and 3.1.0 are currently supported." is shown
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='contextual-alert']//div[contains(text(), 'Unsupported OpenAPI version. Only versions 3.0.x and 3.1.0 are currently supported.')]") should be([visible, 15 s.])
$("By.xpath: //div[@data-test='contextual-alert']//div[contains(text(), 'Unsupported OpenAPI version. Only versions 3.0.x and 3.1.0 are currently supported.')]") should be([visible, 15 s.])
